The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 23: The trade and economic relations committee, headed by Prime Minister Manmohan Singh, today set guidelines for future trade negotiations and enhance the flow of investment into the country. ?The Prime Minister has reviewed various trade agreements and set guidelines for future pacts,? commerce and industry minister Kamal Nath said. 

 New Delhi, June 23: Larsen amp; Toubro today allotted 14,96,149 shares under the employees stock option scheme, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Mumbai, June 23: The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has allowed residents to cancel and rebook forward contracts booked by them to hedge current account transactions, regardless of tenor to provide greater flexibility to residents in managing their exposure.

 Mumbai, June 23: A consortium of state-owned insurance companies led by New India Assurance Co Ltd has won the contract for the annual insurance cover of Air-India. 

 New Delhi, June 23: The government has decided to revamp the drug regulatory structure and set up an independent authority on the lines of the US Food and Drug Administration for quality control of drugs.




